This paper deals with the field of Natural Language Processing (NLP) and Artificial Intelligence (AI), specifically in the area of generating conclusion-supplement answers for non-factoid questions. The paper mentions the use of an attention mechanism, which is commonly used in NLP and AI research. The categories of cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are all relevant sub-categories for this paper.
